<br>
The idea is that right now, every protection spell in the game is cast, either increases our hit points by XX amount for YY mana, lasts a duration, then is gone.  The problem with this is that in a battle, that really doesn't help THAT much, especially if we die without spending all our mana.  So, a new type of shielding that would be caster only is one thing that would be nice.<br>
<br>
Spell name: Magic shield of protection<br>
Classes: Wizard Magician Necro<br>
Mana cost to cast: 1<br>
Duration: 60 minutes or until dispelled<br>
Description: <br>
Through the use of the caster's power, an invisible wall of force that is powered by the caster's mana is created around the caster.  The wall will absorb all types of damage, but in so doing, will drain the caster's mana at a rate of 1 point of mana for each 10 points of damage the caster would have taken, until the caster is out of mana, at which time the effect will end.<br>
<br>
<br>
This spell would aid the casters where if we do agro a mob, we won't go down.  Even in the event of a train, this would allow the caster to run and escape since the effect would stop stuns as well.  It has the disadvantage that the caster WILL go out of mana quickly if he/she does not work to avoid damage.  It has enough of a negative impact in combat where it can't be used to make the casters TOO powerful(you can't just stay in the middle of 5 mobs attacking without going out of mana quickly), but it would also allow the caster to evac a group.  The other aspect is that this spell WOULD allow the evac, but by the time the evac is finished casting, if you have gone too low in mana, you may not be able to cast it anymore.  I feel this would be a very valid compromise.  Now, Necromancers would use their power over life energy to cast this spell, magicians would use elemental energy(non-damage shield) to power theirs, and wizards would use pure energy.  Enchanters already have AoE mezz and stun, so they need this type of spell less than the other pure casters.<br>
<br>
<br>
That's one spell idea and it will get it's share of people who don't like it, but others will probably love the idea.  My next idea may meet with less resistance.<br>
<br>
Skill name: capture energy<br>
Classes: Wizard<br>
Level first available: 34<br>
Description: <br>
The wizard is a master of magical energies, and this allows them to harvest the magical energy around them.  Over time, this ability will capture some of the magical energy of others as it is spent, without being able to drain it directly from other spellcasters.  The ratio of magical energy spent by others to magic gained will increase as the wizard gains more of an understanding of magic.  Since this skill is useless without other spellcasters being near, it will not be very useful in a solo situation.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, both of these would improve the wizard class.  The skill I have in mind isn't mana regeneration in the normal sense, and neither of these ideas would increase damage output directly.  If other classes have the ability to regain mana through various means(Shaman, Necro, enchanter), and we DO have the ability though harvest to capture passive magical energy with the harvest spell, then it makes sense that we could absorb active magical energy as well.<br>
