<br>
Now, the second idea, it takes some of the mana expended by all casters in a set radius(or perhaps a radius based on the wizard's level), and gives it freely to the wizard.  Consider it like harvest, but grabbing the mana as it's being expended by others and claiming it as your own.  It doesn't DRAIN mana, but if a spell takes 400 mana, and is cast by the mob, or another player, we may get anywhere from four to fourty mana suddenly ending up in our mana bar as a freebie.  It's not stealing it, it's just takeing some of the free energy out there.  <br>
<br>
Mana drain, which hurts the target, is not the sort of thing the wizard class should be doing, but if an enchanter casts a spell, there's always going to be some magical energy released into the world that doesn't go into the spell.  It's that energy that the wizards could be tapping in a radius around him/her.  It just seems that unless you fight a spellcasting mob when solo, that you get no benefit from this SKILL(not spell) when isolated away from others, but in a multi-player environment(raid or group), the wizard benefits, which would translate into more nukes that helps the group.<br>
<br>
If I'm still not clear, I'll try it again, but both of these were put together with balance in mind.  Not super-strong, but they touch on what wizards do, and expand on it.<br>
