<br>
This idea is completely different from any spell currently in the game since it is similar to a normal skin spell, but has the cap based on your CURRENT mana, not based on your mana at the time of the casting.  If you have this up, then start chain nukeing down to 20 percent mana(perhaps 600 mana tops), that means you only have 600 mana worth of protection left.  Now, IF you do this, normally you might be able to evac, but if the mob is beating on you, you won't have the 600 mana available, and by the time your evac spell goes off, you won't have the mana left to cast the evac, and you just got your party killed since you can't evac anymore.<br>
<br>
Now, 600 mana at 5 to 1, that's your 3000 damage protection.  Being able to take this additional 3000 damage MIGHT be enough to survive the rest of a nasty encounter, even if the mobs are agroed to you and the rest of your group is alive, but it won't GIVE you a lot since again, casting spells will take away from your ability to stay alive.  Mobs at the higher levels ALL hit for a minimum of 85 damage per hit except for some mobs in Plane of Mischief.  Too powerful?  I really don't think so, it's all a matter of ballance.  If every spell you cast removes some of your ability to defend yourself, then all the better, it's balanced.  It might not be a GOOD idea in places where the mobs AoE, and the mana drain would remove our effectiveness, but for group hunting, this would make us more desired.<br>
